Subject: Re: [T2] Air Cleaners - Stock or Pod-Style?

On Sun, 8 Mar 2009, Zach Ogilvie wrote:

> When I bought my bus it had the pod-style air filter on each carb. I am
> trying to determine whether to keep this setup or track down and install a
> stock air-cleaner. Just wondered what you folks have to say (good, bad or
> ugly) about either setup. I couldn't find anything in the archives...

I'm a great believer in stock air cleaners.  The pod-style filters are a 
compromise to allow easy fitment to a wide variety of applications but 
they are deficient in cleaning ability, particularly with fine particles.

George
